
# Showcase Product PRD Documentation

## 1. Overview
Showcase is a visually stunning product display page designed to highlight key features, specifications, and benefits of digital/physical products with elegant presentation elements.

## 2. Product Objectives
- Create immersive product viewing experience
- Highlight key features through visual storytelling
- Provide clear CTAs for conversions
- Maintain responsive design across devices
- Support multimedia content integration

## 3. Core Features

### 3.1 Hero Section
- Full-width high resolution product image/video background
- Overlay with concise product tagline (max 8 words)
- Prominent CTA button (primary action)
- Secondary CTA option

### 3.2 Product Gallery
- Interactive image carousel with:
  - Thumbnail navigation
  - Zoom functionality
  - 360° rotation capability (for physical products)
  - Video demonstration integration
- Color/size variant selector (if applicable)

### 3.3 Feature Highlights
- Icon-based feature grid (3-6 key features)
- Hover animations showing brief explanations
- Visual indicators for premium features

### 3.4 Specifications Panel
- Tabbed interface for:
  - Technical specs
  - Compatibility info
  - Package contents
  - Dimensions/weight
- Downloadable spec sheets (PDF)

### 3.5 Social Proof Section
- Integrated review snippets (5-star display)
- Customer testimonial carousel
- Trust badges/security certifications

### 3.6 Dynamic Pricing Module
- Real-time price display
- Discount/savings calculator
- Subscription options (if applicable)
- Payment method icons

## 4. Technical Requirements

### 4.1 Frontend
- React.js framework
- GSAP for animations
- Responsive breakpoints:
  - Mobile (<768px)
  - Tablet (768-1024px)
  - Desktop (>1024px)
- WebP image format support
- Lazy loading implementation

### 4.2 Performance
- Page load time <2s
- Lighthouse score >90
- CDN integration for assets
- Critical CSS inlining

### 4.3 Analytics
- Google Analytics 4 integration
- Hotjar heatmaps
- Conversion funnel tracking
- Scroll depth measurement

## 5. User Flows

### 5.1 Primary Flow
Hero → Gallery → Features → Specs → CTA

### 5.2 Secondary Flow
Social Proof → Pricing → CTA

## 6. Success Metrics
- Conversion rate (target >8%)
- Average time on page (>90s)
- Gallery interaction rate (>60%)
- Scroll depth (>70% to CTA)

## 7. Accessibility
- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader optimization
- Color contrast validation
- Reduced motion option

## 8. Localization
- RTL language support
- Currency/locale detection
- Translated content slots
- Localized imagery options

## 9. Maintenance
- CMS integration points
- Scheduled content updates
- A/B testing framework
- Emergency update protocol
